entries.title: A New Cycloartanyl Ester from the Roots of Codonopsis pilosula and Its Anti-Inflammatory Activity

title_detail.value: A New Cycloartanyl Ester from the Roots of Codonopsis pilosula and Its Anti-Inflammatory Activity

entries.summary: A new cycloartanyl ester, named codonopilate D (1), was isolated from the roots of Codonopsis pilosula (Franch.) Nannf. The structure of compound 1 was elucidated by extensive spectroscopic analysis including UV, IR, MS, and NMR data. Compound 1 exhibited the potential of inhibiting LPS-induced NO production in RAW 264.7 cells.

entries.title: Two New Depsidones from Parmelia saxatili s

title_detail.value: Two New Depsidones from Parmelia saxatili s

entries.summary: Two new depsidones, diffractione B (1) and salazinin A (2), and two known compounds, the dibenzofuran derivative usnic acid (3) and depsidone salazinic acid (4), were isolated from Parmelia saxatilis. The structures of the isolated compounds were identified by spectral analysis and comparison with literature data.

entries.title: A New Prenylated Flavanonol from the Roots of Sophora flavescens

title_detail.value: A New Prenylated Flavanonol from the Roots of Sophora flavescens

entries.summary: A new prenylated flavanonol, (2R,3R)-8-isopentenyl-5-methoxy-7,2′,4′-trihydroxyflavanonol (1) was isolated from the roots of Sophora flavescens. The structure was elucidated on the basis of spectroscopic data. Compound 1 exhibited moderate inhibition towards HeLa, HepG2, and HL-60 tumor cell lines at 14.3, 19.2, 31.5 μg/mL, respectively.

entries.title: A New Phenolic Glycoside from Polygonatum Sibiricum and its α-Glucosidase Inhibitory Activity

title_detail.value: A New Phenolic Glycoside from Polygonatum Sibiricum and its α-Glucosidase Inhibitory Activity

entries.summary: A new phenolic glycoside 1, together with two known compounds (2, 3), has been isolated from the ethanolic extract of Polygonatum sibiricum F. Delaroche. Its structure was elucidated as (2R)-syringylpropane-1,3-diol-1-O-β-D-glucopyranoside by spectroscopic data (1H NMR, 13C NMR, HSQC, HMBC, and HR-ESI-MS) and chemical evidence. In the in vitro assay, compound 1 displayed potent inhibitory activity against α-glucosidase with an IC50 value of 10.90 μM.

entries.title: A Novel Naphthopyrone-Derived Metabolite from the Marine Crinoid Comanthus bennetti

title_detail.value: A Novel Naphthopyrone-Derived Metabolite from the Marine Crinoid Comanthus bennetti

entries.summary: One novel naphthopyrone-derived metabolite, named bennepyrone A (1), was isolated from a marine crinoid Comanthus bennetti. The structure of the compound was elucidated on the basis of its spectroscopic data and comparison with those of comaparvin. Compound 1 possesses a new carbon skeleton that is derived from the naphthopyrone skeleton.

entries.title: Quinone Derivatives from the Soft Coral Sinularia scabra

title_detail.value: Quinone Derivatives from the Soft Coral Sinularia scabra

entries.summary: One new quinone derivative, 1′,2′-epoxyflexibilisquinone (1), and one known quinone compound, flexibilisquinone (2), were isolated from the wild-type soft coral Sinularia scabra. The structures of both compounds 1 and 2 were established by 1D and 2D NMR spectroscopic data analysis and comparison with the reported data.

entries.title: A New Triterpenoid Saponin from Clematis akebioides

title_detail.value: A New Triterpenoid Saponin from Clematis akebioides

entries.summary: A new triterpenoid saponin and nine known compounds were isolated from the aerial parts of Clematis akebioides. The structures of these compounds were determined using spectroscopic methods and comparison with the literature. All of these compounds were obtained from C. akebioides for the first time.

entries.title: Phenolic Constituents with their α-Glucosidase Inhibitory Activities from the Leaves of Viburnum melanocarpum

title_detail.value: Phenolic Constituents with their α-Glucosidase Inhibitory Activities from the Leaves of Viburnum melanocarpum

entries.summary: A new compound 1, together with two known compounds (2, 3), has been isolated from the ethanolic extract of Viburnum melanocarpum leaves. Their structures were elucidated by extensive spectroscopic evidence and chemical method. In the in vitro assay, compounds 1 and 3 displayed potent inhibitory activity against α-glucosidase with IC50 values of 6.28 μM and 12.73 μM, respectively.
